is enriched with a practice-based methodology informed by the author’s own practice and based on extensive conversations with leading sound practitioners in the Indian subcontinent. The book locates an emerging social and spatial awareness in Indian film and media production aided by a creative practice of sound, occurring alongside the traditionally transcendental, oral, and pluriversal approach to listening. By tracing this confluence of tradition and modernity, the book makes valuable contributions to the fields of film history, sound, and media studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture industryzIndia. 0aSound in motion pictures. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aInterdisciplinary Studies. 4aMedia Studies. 4aRadio and Television. 4aSouth Asia. 4aTransnational and Global Studies. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aFilm, Media and Communication, Asian Studies, Indian Cinema, Film History, Sound Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048551668?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048551668423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048551668/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles